g.text: Products from sawmillsThe timber coming out of the saw mill is further processed to construction timber, panels and furniture. This ist the way the wood gains most value in the country itself. For this reason it makes sense to establish this business before all others.Products from pulp millsProducts of pulp mills are paper products for hygiene, writing, printing and packaging.Products in the future But new technologies are creating many more ways to use wood. It is a great oppurtunity to figure out how to repalce products out of not renewable resources with products made out of wood. What kind of industries will appear? And how can the exsiting get more sustaible und sufficient? How to combine different industries to get a more stable network? As a location, Fauske has good prerequisites for taking steps in this direction. It has the natural resources, the area and the framework conditions to become a role model for other regions. However, investors and a well-trained workforce are needed.Quantity of wood required for further processing industry in FauskeConstruction timber: 200 sawlogs or moreBoards and panels: 500 - 2000 sawlogs ore moreFurniture: raw material will most likely be purchased from sawmills in Sweden or other parts of Norway
